&lt;del&gt;Commit: e2c5a0faaa6e2405e27575935fc8a96b8510bf8c&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="393213" author="dongyang" created="Thu, 16 Nov 2023 00:26:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should be fixed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/48080&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/48080&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16057&quot; title=&quot;OBD_MD_FLGROUP not set for ladvise rpc&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16057&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16057&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; obdclass: set OBD_MD_FLGROUP for ladvise RPC&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="367037" author="adilger" created="Thu, 23 Mar 2023 11:08:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Zam, I agree.  The ladvise request could be dropped in this case, rather than taking the system down. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="366621" author="zam" created="Tue, 21 Mar 2023 10:46:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wouldn&apos;t be possible to ignore ladvise requests if the object is not fully initialised? it is an optional hint, not a real read request as in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15139&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_160h: dt_record_write() ASSERTION( dt-&amp;gt;do_body_ops-&amp;gt;dbo_write ) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15139&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15139&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="330286" author="sthiell" created="Fri, 25 Mar 2022 19:39:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Interesting, ok I&apos;m now watching &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15139&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_160h: dt_record_write() ASSERTION( dt-&amp;gt;do_body_ops-&amp;gt;dbo_write ) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15139&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15139&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And very cool, I didn&apos;t know about the clone repo on Github, this is going to be useful, thanks!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="330278" author="adilger" created="Fri, 25 Mar 2022 18:30:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at the code in 2.12.8 (and master) I see that &quot;&lt;tt&gt;.dbo_ladvise = osd_ladvise&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is set in the object methods, so this assertion is very strange.  I was likewise unable to reproduce this issue on my test system, even with a directory or symlink, or with a PFL file that had an uninstantiated layout in the &quot;advice&quot; range.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15139&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_160h: dt_record_write() ASSERTION( dt-&amp;gt;do_body_ops-&amp;gt;dbo_write ) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-15139&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-15139&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which is a similar &lt;tt&gt;LASSERT()&lt;/tt&gt; for missing object operations that is unexplained so far.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PS: you should fork your lustre github repo from &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/lustre/lustre-release&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;lustre/lustre-release&lt;/a&gt;, which is the clone that I maintain from the whamcloud.com repo.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
